---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const title = "Accessibility Statement - Accessible Outdoors";
const description = "Our commitment to digital accessibility for all users.";
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} showSidebar={false}>
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto prose prose-green prose-lg py-12">
    <h1>Accessibility Statement</h1>
    <p class="lead">Last Updated: December 22, 2025</p>

    <p>Accessible Outdoors is committed to ensuring digital accessibility for people with disabilities. We are continually improving the user experience for everyone and applying the relevant accessibility standards.</p>

    <h2>Conformance Status</h2>
    <p>The <a href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/standards-guidelines/wcag/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG)</a> defines requirements for designers and developers to improve accessibility for people with disabilities. It defines three levels of conformance: Level A, Level AA, and Level AAA.</p>
    <p>Accessible Outdoors is partially conformant with WCAG 2.1 level AA. Partially conformant means that some parts of the content do not fully conform to the accessibility standard, though we strive for full compliance.</p>

    <h2>Feedback</h2>
    <p>We welcome your feedback on the accessibility of Accessible Outdoors. Please let us know if you encounter accessibility barriers on our site:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>E-mail: accessibility@accessibleoutdoors.com</li>
    </ul>
    <p>We try to respond to feedback within 2 business days.</p>

    <h2>Technical Specifications</h2>
    <p>Accessibility of Accessible Outdoors relies on the following technologies to work with the particular combination of web browser and any assistive technologies or plugins installed on your computer:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>HTML</li>
      <li>WAI-ARIA</li>
      <li>CSS</li>
      <li>JavaScript</li>
    </ul>
    <p>These technologies are relied upon for conformance with the accessibility standards used.</p>

    <h2>Assessment Approach</h2>
    <p>Accessible Outdoors assessed the accessibility of this website by the following approaches:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Self-evaluation</li>
      <li>Automated testing via Lighthouse and axe-core</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Known Limitations</h2>
    <p>Despite our best efforts to ensure accessibility of Accessible Outdoors, there may be some limitations. Below is a description of known limitations and potential solutions. Please contact us if you observe an issue not listed below.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Map Integrations:</strong> Some third-party map embeds may not be fully accessible to screen readers. We provide text-based alternatives and direct links to Google Maps for better navigation support.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</Layout>
